            <p class="text-lg text-left font-normal md:w-10/12 mb-4">Elmiron is a prescription drug used to treat what is commonly called “painful bladder syndrome,” and interstitial cystitis.</p>
            <p class="text-lg text-left font-normal md:w-10/12 mb-4">It has been prescribed to treat osteoarthritis and is used as a coagulant as well.</p>
            <p class="text-lg text-left font-normal md:w-10/12 mb-4">This drug has been widely prescribed for decades and has been used by hundreds of thousands of individuals.</p>
            <p class="text-lg text-left font-normal md:w-10/12 mb-4">Many users of Elmiron take the drug for long periods of time, often using the drug for many years.</p>
            <p class="text-lg text-left font-normal md:w-10/12 mb-4">Recently, a trend has been identified of Elmiron patients developing an eye condition called maculopathy.</p>
            <p class="text-lg text-left font-normal md:w-10/12 mb-4">Maculopathy is a term that covers a number of conditions that affect the macula, which is part of the retina.</p>
            <p class="text-lg text-left font-normal md:w-10/12 mb-4">This part of the eye controls highly sensitive vision, such as focusing and reading.</p>    
            <p class="text-lg text-left font-normal md:w-10/12 mb-4">A study conducted by the American Academy of Ophthalmology showed that about a quarter of the patients observed with significant exposure to Elmiron showed signs of eye damage specifically to the retina.</p>
            <p class="text-lg text-left font-normal md:w-10/12 mb-4">Those whose dosage was the highest also were among the most likely to exhibit damage to the macula.</p>
            <p class="text-lg text-left font-normal md:w-10/12 mb-4">The doctors who performed this study believe that use of the drug is toxic to the macula and creating vision damage with prolonged exposure.</p>
            <p class="text-lg text-left font-normal md:w-10/12 mb-8">There have also been recent reports indicating that in some cases, patients that do not report any vision symptoms have evidence of damage to the retina</p>
            <ul class="mb-4 md:w-10/12 hidden">
                <li class="px-4 py-2 box-shadow text-lg font-medium mb-4 rounded border-solid border border-gray-200"><span class="text-red-600">1.</span> The device doesn’t lock the lid properly (although it seems locked), and the user is able to take the lid off before the pressure has been released.</li>
                <li class="px-4 py-2 box-shadow text-lg font-medium mb-4 rounded border-solid border border-gray-200"><span class="text-red-600">2.</span> The device indicates that all the pressure has been released, when in fact the release valve was clogged and the pressure was not fully released.</li>
                <li class="px-4 py-2 box-shadow text-lg font-medium mb-4 rounded border-solid border border-gray-200"><span class="text-red-600">3.</span> The device explodes at some point during use.</li>
