            <p class="text-md text-left text-xl font-normal md:w-10/12 mb-3">Maculopathy is a term that covers any disease or condition that damages the macula.</p>
            <p class="text-md text-left text-xl font-normal md:w-10/12 mb-4">The type of this condition caused by Elmiron has a couple symptoms to watch out for:</p>
            <p class="text-md text-left text-xl font-bold md:w-10/12 mb-3">1. Trouble focusing vision for tasks such as reading</p>
            <p class="text-md text-left text-xl font-normal md:w-10/12 mb-4">- Damage to the macula can make it difficult for individuals to focus their vision to read.</p>
            <p class="text-md text-left text-xl font-bold md:w-10/12 mb-3">2. Sensitivity to light or changes in lighting</p>
            <p class="text-md text-left text-xl font-normal md:w-10/12 mb-4">- Maculopathy and damage to the macula can also make it difficult or painful for the eyes when adjusting to light or being exposed to bright light.</p>
            <p class="text-md text-left text-xl font-bold md:w-10/12 mb-3">3. Dark spots on the retina, that can be observed during an eye examination.</p>
            <p class="text-md text-left text-xl font-normal md:w-10/12 mb-4">- These spots are difficult to see without the proper medical equipment and we recommend any individual who believes they are at risk have an examination performed by a medical professional.</p>
